OL,5, Regulated train fares in England will  
OL,6, again rise below the rate of inflation 
OL,7, next year, the government has said.    
OL,9,FThe move is meant to help people with  
OL,10,Fthe soaring cost of living and follows 
OL,11,Fa similar intervention in 2023.        
OL,13,FAny rises will once more be delayed    
OL,14,Funtil March 2024, rather than kicking  
OL,15,Fin in January as was normal pre-Covid. 
OL,17,FHowever, one campaign group said fares 
OL,18,Fshould be frozen "in recognition of the
OL,19,Fburden high fares place on rail        
OL,20,Fpassengers".                           
